<li><cite class="citation web"><a href="/wiki/Russ_Roberts" title="Russ Roberts">Roberts, Russ</a> (June 10, 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.econtalk.org/archives/_featuring/bruce_schneier/">"Schneier on Power, the Internet, and Security"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/EconTalk" title="EconTalk">EconTalk</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Library_of_Economics_and_Liberty" title="Library of Economics and Liberty">Library of Economics and Liberty</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABruce+Schneier&amp;rft.atitle=Schneier+on+Power%2C+the+Internet%2C+and+Security&amp;rft.aufirst=Russ&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.date=2013-06-10&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.econtalk.org%2Farchives%2F_featuring%2Fbruce_schneier%2F&amp;rft.jtitle=EconTalk&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m3NJ-Ow2Lvg">Bruce Schneier at Google</a>, 19 June 2013. Schneier discusses various aspects of Internet computing and global geo-politics including trust, power relations, control, cooperative systems, ethics, laws, and security technologies. (55 minutes)</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.well.com/conf/inkwell.vue/topics/452/Bruce-Schneier-Liars-and-Outlier-page01.html">Bruce Schneier interviewed</a> on <a href="/wiki/The_WELL" title="The WELL">The WELL</a> by <a href="/wiki/Jon_Lebkowsky" title="Jon Lebkowsky">Jon Lebkowsky</a>, August 2012</li>
</ul>
